Aim:
To check if a given number is even or odd.

Algorithm:
Start
Read a number
If number % 2 == 0 → Even
Else → Odd
Stop

Program:
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    int n;
    cout<<"Enter a number: ";
    cin>>n;
    if(n % 2 == 0)
        cout<<"Even Number";
    else
        cout<<"Odd Number";
    return 0;
}

Sample Output:
Enter a number: 7
Odd Number

Result:
The program successfully checks whether a number is even or odd.

